obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (30015)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30015&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Parsi Marriage and`
  line `Divorce Act, 1936.`
  line
  line `(2) ^1[It extends to the whole of India except the State of Jammu and Kashmir*:]`
  line
  line `Provided that the Central Government may, in respect of ^2[territories which, immediately before the`
  line `1st November, 1956, were comprised in Part B States] by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that`
  line `the provisions of this Act relating to the constitution and powers of Parsi Matrimonial Courts and to`
  line `appeals from the decisions and orders of such Courts shall apply with such modifications as may be`
  line `specified in the notification:`
  line
  line `^3[Provided further that nothing contained in this Act shall apply to the Renoncants of the Union`
  line `territory of Pondicherry.]`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date^4 as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule for It extends to the whole of India except Part B States and, in respect of Parsi`
  line `citizens of India, to the whole of India (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956, for Part B States.`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 26 of 1968, s. 3 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 24-5-1968).`
  line `4. 22nd June, 1936; see Gazette of India, 1936, Part I, p.621.`
  line `*. Vide Notification No. S.O. 3912 (E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (30016)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30016&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless there is anything repugnant in the subject or context,--`
  line
  line `(1) "Chief Justice" includes senior Judge;`
  line
  line `(2) "Court" means a Court constituted under this Act;`
  line
  line `(3) to "desert" together with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means to desert`
  line `the other party to a marriage without reasonable cause and without the consent, or against the will, of`
  line `such party;`
  line
  line `(4) "grievous hurt" means--`
  line
  line `(a) emasculation;`
  line
  line `(b) permanent privation of the sight of either eye;`
  line
  line `(c) permanent privation of the hearing of either ear;`
  line
  line `(d) privation of any member or joint;`
  line
  line `(e) destruction or permanent impairing of the powers of any member or joint;`
  line
  line `(f) permanent disfiguration of the head or face; or`
  line
  line `(g) any hurt which endangers life;`
  line
  line `(5) "husband" means a Parsi husband;`
  line
  line `(6) "marriage" means a marriage between Parsis whether contracted before or after the`
  line `commencement of this Act;`
  line
  line `(7) a "Parsi" means a Parsi Zoroastrian;`
  line
  line `(8) "priest" means a Parsi priest and includes Dastur and Mobed; and`
  line
  line `(9) "wife" means a Parsi wife.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (30017)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Requisites to validity of Parsi marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30017&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] No marriage shall be valid if--`
  line
  line `(a) the contracting parties are related to each other in any of the degrees of consanguinity or`
  line `affinity set forth in Schedule I; or`
  line
  line `(b) such marriage is not solemnized according to the Parsi form of ceremony called`
  line `"Ashirvad"`
  line `by a priest in the presence of two Parsi witnesses other than such priest; or`
  line
  line `^2[(c) in the case of any Parsi (whether such Parsi has changed his or her religion or domicile or`
  line `not) who, if a male, has not completed twenty-one years of age, and if a female, has not completed`
  line `eighteen years of age.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Notwithstanding that a marriage is invalid under any of the provisions of sub-section (1), any`
  line `child of such marriage who would have been legitimate if the marriage had been valid, shall be`
  line legitimate.]
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 3 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 5 of 1988, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 2, ibid., for clause (c) (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (30018)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Remarriage when unlawful.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Rep. by Act 3 of 1936, s. 53 (w.e.f. 23-4-1936).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30018&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) No Parsi (whether such Parsi has changed his or her religion or`
  line `domicile or not) shall contract any marriage under this Act or any other law in the lifetime of his or her`
  line `wife or husband, whether a Parsi or not, except after his or her lawful divorce from such wife or husband`
  line `or after his or her marriage with such wife or husband has lawfully been declared null and void or`
  line `dissolved, and, if the marriage was contracted with such wife or husband under the Parsi Marriage and`
  line `Divorce Act 1865^1(15 of 1865), or under this Act, except after a divorce, declaration or dissolution as`
  line `aforesaid under either of the said Acts.`
  line
  line `(2) Every marriage contracted contrary to the provisions of sub-section (1) shall be void.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (30019)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Punishment of bigamy.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30019&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `Every Parsi who during the lifetime of his or her wife or husband,`
  line `whether a Parsi or not, contracts a marriage without having been lawfully divorced from such wife or`
  line `husband, or without his or her marriage with such wife or husband having legally been declared null and`
  line `void or dissolved, shall be subject to the penalties provided in sections 494 and 495 of the Indian Penal`
  line `Code (45 of 1860) for the offence of marrying again during the lifetime of a husband or wife.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (30020)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Certificate and registry of marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30020&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `Every marriage contracted under this Act shall,`
  line `immediately on the solemnization thereof, be certified by the officiating priest in the form contained in`
  line `Schedule II. The certificate shall be signed by the said priest, the contracting parties ^1*** and two`
  line `witnesses present at the marriage and the said priest shall thereupon send such certificate together with a`
  line `fee of two rupees to be paid by the husband to the Registrar of the place at which such marriage is`
  line `solemnized. The Registrar on receipt of the certificate and fee shall enter the certificate in a register to be`
  line `kept by him for that purpose and shall be entitled to retain the fee.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words ", or their fathers or guardians when they shall not have completed the age of twenty-one years," omitted by Act 5`
  line `of 1988, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (30021)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Appointment of Registrar.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30021&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `For the purposes of this Act a Registrar shall be appointed. Within`
  line `the local limits of the ordinary original civil jurisdiction of a High Court, the Registrar shall be appointed`
  line `by the Chief Justice of such Court, and without such limits, by the State Government. Every Registrar so`
  line `appointed may be removed by the Chief Justice or State Government appointing him.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (30022)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Marriage register to be open for public inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30022&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `The register of marriages mentioned in`
  line `section 6 shall, at all reasonable times, be open for inspection, and certified extracts therefrom shall, on`
  line `application, be given by the Registrar on payment to him by the applicant of two rupees for each such`
  line `extract. Every such register shall be evidence of the truth of the statements therein contained.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (30023)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Copy of certificate to sent to Registrar-General of Births, Deaths and Marriages.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30023&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line Every
  line `Registrar, except the Registrar appointed by the Chief Justice of the High Court of Judicature at Bombay,`
  line `shall, at such intervals as the State Government by which he was appointed from time to time directs,`
  line `send to the Registrar-General of Births, Deaths and Marriages for the territories administered by such`
  line `State Government a true copy certified by him in such form as such State Government from time to time`
  line `prescribes of all certificates entered by him in the said register of marriages since the last of such`
  line intervals.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (30024)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Registration of divorces.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30024&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `When a Court passes a decree for divorce, nullity or dissolution, the`
  line `Court shall send a copy of the decree for registration to the Registrar of Marriages within its jurisdiction`
  line `appointed under section 7; the Registrar shall enter the same in a register to be kept by him for the`
  line `purpose, and the provisions of Part II applicable to the Registrars and registers of marriages shall be`
  line `applicable, so far as may be, to the Registrars and registers of divorces and decrees of nullity and`
  line dissolution.
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (30025)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Penalty for solemnizing marriage contrary to section 4.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30025&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `Any priest knowingly and wilfully`
  line `solemnizing any marriage contrary to and in violation of section 4 shall, on conviction thereof, be`
  line `punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may`
  line `extend to two hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (30026)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Penalty for priest’s neglect of requirements of section 6.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30026&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Any priest neglecting to comply`
  line `with any of the requisitions affecting him contained in section 6 shall, on conviction thereof, be punished`
  line `for every such offence with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with`
  line `fine which may extend to one hundred rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (30027)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Penalty for omitting to subscribe and attest certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30027&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Every other person required by`
  line `section 6 to subscribe or attest the said certificate who shall wilfully omit or neglect so to do, shall, on`
  line `conviction thereof, be punished for every such offence with a fine not exceeding one hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (30028)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Penalty for making, etc., false certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30028&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Every person making or signing or attesting any`
  line `such certificate containing a statement which is false, and which he either knows or believes to be false,`
  line `shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to three months, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to one hundred rupees, or with both; and if the act amounts to forgery as defined in the`
  line `Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860), then such person shall also be liable, on conviction thereof, to the`
  line `penalties provided in section 466 of the said Code.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (30029)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Penalty for failing to register certificate.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30029&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `Any Registrar failing to enter the said certificate`
  line `pursuant to section 6 shall be punished with simple imprisonment for a term which may extend to one`
  line `year, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or with both.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (30030)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Penalty for secreting, destroying or altering register.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30030&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Any person secreting, destroying, or`
  line `dishonestly or fraudulently altering the said register in any part thereof, shall be punished with`
  line `imprisonment of either description as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860) for a term which may`
  line `extend to two years or if he be a Register, for a term which may extend to five years and shall also be`
  line `liable to fine which may extend to five hundred rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (30031)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Formal irregularity not to invalidate marriage.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30031&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No marriage contracted under this Act shall`
  line `be deemed to be invalid solely by reason of the fact that it was not certified under section 6, or that the`
  line `certificate was not sent to the Registrar, or that the certificate was defective, irregular or incorrect.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (30032)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Constitution of Special Courts under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30032&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `For the purpose of hearing suits under this Act,`
  line `a Special Court shall be constituted in each of the Presidency-towns of Calcutta, Madras and Bombay,`
  line `and in such other places in the territories of the several State Governments as such Governments`
  line `respectively shall think fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (30033)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Parsi Chief Matrimonial Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 4, for "by seven delegates" (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30033&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Court so constituted in each of the Presidency-towns`
  line `shall be entitled the Parsi Chief Matrimonial Court of Calcutta, Madras or Bombay, as the case may be.`
  line `The local limits of the jurisdiction of a Parsi Chief Matrimonial Court shall be coterminous with the local`
  line `limits of the ordinary original civil jurisdiction of the High Court. The Chief Justice of the High Court, or`
  line `such other Judge of the same Court as the Chief Justice shall from time to time appoint shall be the Judge`
  line `of such Matrimonial Court, and, in the trial of cases under this Act, he shall be aided ^1[by five delegates,`
  line `except in regard to—`
  line
  line `(a) interlocutory applications and proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) alimony and maintenance, both permanent as well as pendente lite;`
  line
  line `(c) custody, maintenance and education of children; and`
  line
  line `(d) all matters and proceedings other than the regular hearing of cases.]`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (30034)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Parsi District Matrimonial Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 4, for "by seven delegates" (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30034&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `Every Court so constituted at a place other than a`
  line `Presidency-town shall be entitled the Parsi District Matrimonial Court of such place. Subject to the`
  line `provisions contained in section 21, the local limits of the jurisdiction of such Court shall be coterminous`
  line `with the limits of the district in which it is held. The Judge of the principal Court of original civil`
  line `jurisdiction at such place shall be the Judge of such Matrimonial Court, and in the trial of cases under this`
  line `Act he shall be aided ^1[by five delegates, except in regard to`
  line
  line `(a) interlocutory applications and proceedings;`
  line
  line `(b) alimony and maintenance, both permanent as well as pendente lite;`
  line
  line `(c) custody, maintenance and education of children; and`
  line
  line `(d) all matters and proceedings other than the regular hearing of cases.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (30035)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to alter territorial jurisdiction of District Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30035&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The State Government may from`
  line `time to time alter the local limits of the jurisdiction of any Parsi District Matrimonial Court, and may`
  line `include within such limits any number of districts under its government.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (30036)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Certain districts to be within jurisdiction of the Chief Matrimonial Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30036&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Any district`
  line `which the State Government, on account of the fewness of its Parsi inhabitants, shall deem it inexpedient`
  line `to include within the jurisdiction of any District Matrimonial Court, shall be included within the`
  line `jurisdiction of the Parsi Chief Matrimonial Court for the territories under such State Government where`
  line `there is such a Court.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (30037)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Court seal.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30037&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `A seal shall be made for every Court constituted under this Act, and all decrees and`
  line `orders and copies of decrees and orders of such Court shall be sealed with such seal, which shall be kept`
  line `in the custody of the presiding Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (30038)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Appointment of delegates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30038&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) The State Governments, shall, in the Presidency-towns and`
  line `districts subject to their respective governments, respectively appoint persons to be delegates to aid in the`
  line `adjudication of cases arising under this Act, after giving the local parsis an opportunity of expressing their`
  line `opinion in such manner as the respective Governments may think fit.`
  line
  line `(2) The persons so appointed shall be Parsis, their names shall be published in the Official Gazette`
  line `and their number shall, within the local limits of the ordinary original civil jurisdiction of a High Court,`
  line `be not more than thirty, and in districts beyond such limits, not more than twenty.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (30039)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to appoint new delegates.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 5 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30039&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `The appointment of a delegate shall be for ten years; but he`
  line `shall be eligible for reappointment for the like term or terms. Whenever a delegate shall die, or have`
  line `completed his term of office, or be desirous of relinquishing his office, or refuse or become incapable or`
  line `unfit to act, or cease to be a Parsi, or be convicted of an offence under the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860)`
  line `or other law for the time being in force ^1[involving moral turpitude], or be adjudged insolvent, then and so`
  line `often the State Government may appoint any person being a Parsi, to be a delegate in his stead, and the`
  line `name of the person so appointed shall be published in the Official Gazette.`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (30040)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Delegates to be deemed public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30040&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `All delegates appointed under this Act shall be`
  line `considered to be public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (30041)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Selection of delegates under sections 19 and 20 to be from those appointed under section 24.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for "three" (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30041&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `The delegates selected under sections 19 and 20 to aid in the adjudication of suits under this Act,`
  line `shall be taken under the orders of the presiding Judge of the Court in due rotation from the delegates`
  line `appointed by the State Government under section 24:`
  line
  line `Provided that each party to the suit may, without cause assigned, challenge any ^1[two] of the`
  line `delegates attending the Court before such delegates are selected and no delegate so challenged shall be`
  line selected.
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (30042)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 28
  title `Practitioners in Matrimonial Courts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30042&sectionno=28&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `All legal practitioners entitled to practise in a High`
  line `Court shall be entitled to practise in any Court constituted under this Act, and all legal practitioners`
  line `entitled to practise in a District Court shall be entitled to practise in any Parsi District Matrimonial Court`
  line `constituted under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (30043)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 29
  title `Court in which suits to be brought.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30043&sectionno=29&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `(1) All suits instituted under this Act shall be brought in`
  line `the Court within the limits of whose jurisdiction the defendant resides at the time of the institution of the`
  line `suit ^1[or where the marriage under this Act was solemnized.]`
  line
  line `(2) When the defendant shall at such time have left ^2[the territories to which this Act extends] such`
  line `suit shall be brought in the Court at the place where the plaintiff and defendant last resided together.`
  line
  line `(3) In any case, whether the defendant resides in ^2[the territories to which this Act extends] or not,`
  line `such suit may be brought in the Court at the place where the plaintiff resides or at the place where the`
  line `plaintiff and the defendant last resided together, if such Court, after recording its reasons in writing,`
  line `grants leave so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_29_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Added by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule for "Part A States and Part C States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (30044)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 30
  title `Suits for nullity.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30044&sectionno=30&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `In any case in which consummation of the marriage is from natural causes`
  line `impossible, such marriage may, at the instance of either party thereto, be declared to be null and void.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (30045)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 31
  title `Suits for dissolution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30045&sectionno=31&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `If a husband or wife shall have been continually absent from his or her`
  line `wife or husband for the space of seven years, and shall not have been heard of as being alive within that`
  line `time by those persons who would have naturally heard of him or her, had he or she been alive, the`
  line `marriage of such husband or wife may, at the instance of either party thereto, be dissolved.`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (30046)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 32
  title `Grounds for divorce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30046&sectionno=32&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `Any married person may sue for divorce on any one or more of the`
  line `following grounds, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) that the marriage has not been consummated within one year after its solemnization owing to`
  line `the wilful refusal of the defendant to consummate it;`
  line
  line `(b) that the defendant at the time of the marriage was of unsound mind and has been habitually so`
  line `up to the date of the suit:`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground, unless the plaintiff (1) was ignorant of`
  line `the fact at the time of the marriage, and (2) has filed the suit within three years from the date of the`
  line marriage;
  line
  line `^1[(bb) that the defendant has been incurably of unsound mind for a period of two years or`
  line `upwards immediately preceding the filing of the suit or has been suffering continuously or`
  line `intermittently from mental disorder of such kind and to such an extent that the plaintiff cannot`
  line `reasonably be expected to live with the defendant.`
  line
  line `Explanation.In this clause,--`
  line
  line `(a) the expression "mental disorder" means mental illness, arrested or incomplete`
  line `development of mind, psychopathic disorder or any other disorder or disability of mind and`
  line `includes schizophrenia;`
  line
  line `(b) the expression "psychopathic disorder" means a persistent disorder or disability of mind`
  line `(whether or not including subnormality of intelligence) which results in abnormally aggressive or`
  line `seriously irresponsible conduct on the part of the defendant, and whether or not it requires or is`
  line `susceptible to medical treatment;`
  line
  line `(c) that the defendant was at the time of marriage pregnant by some person other than the`
  line `plaintiff:`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground, unless (1) the plaintiff was at the`
  line `time of the marriage ignorant of the fact alleged, (2) the suit has been filed within two years of`
  line `the date of marriage, and (3) marital intercourse has not taken place after the plaintiff came to`
  line `know of the fact;`
  line
  line `(d) that the defendant has since the marriage committed adultery or fornication or bigamy or`
  line `rape or an unnatural offence:`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground if the suit has been filed more than`
  line `two years after the plaintiff came to know of the fact;`
  line
  line `^2[(dd) that the different has since the solemnization of the marriage treated the plaintiff with`
  line `cruelty or has behaved in such a way as to render it in the judgment of the Court improper to`
  line `compel the plaintiff to live with the defendant:`
  line
  line `Provided that in every suit for divorce on this ground it shall be in the discretion of the Court`
  line `whether it should grant a decree for divorce or for judicial separation only;]`
  line
  line `(e) that the defendant has since the marriage voluntarily caused grievous hurt to the plaintiff`
  line `or has infected the plaintiff with venereal disease or, where the defendant is the husband, has`
  line `compelled the wife to submit herself to prostitution:`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground, if the suit has been filed more than`
  line `two years (i) after the infliction of the grievous hurt, or (ii) after the plaintiff came to know of the`
  line `infection, or (iii) after the last act of compulsory prostitution;`
  line
  line `(f) that the defendant is undergoing a sentence of imprisonment for seven years or more for`
  line `an offence as defined in the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860):`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground, unless the defendant has prior to`
  line `the filing of the suit undergone at least one years imprisonment out of the said period;`
  line
  line `(g) that the defendant has deserted the plaintiff for at least ^3[two years];`
  line
  line `(h) that ^5*** an order has been passed against the defendant by a Magistrate awarding`
  line `separate maintenance to the plaintiff, and the parties have not had marital intercourse for ^6[one year] or more since such decree or order;`
  line
  line `^7* * ** *`
  line
  line `(j) that the defendant has ceased to be a Parsi ^8[by conversion to another religion:]`
  line
  line `Provided that divorce shall not be granted on this ground if the suit has been filed more than`
  line `two years after the plaintiff came to know of the fact.`
obj_root_law_sections_32_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 3 of 1951, s. 3 and the Schedule for "Part A States and Part C States" (w.e.f. 1-4-1951).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for three years (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `4. The words a decree or order for judicial separation has been passed against the defendant, or omitted by s. 8, ibid.`
  line `(w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid/i@., for three years (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `6. Clause (i) omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `7. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_a:
  sectionId (30047)
  sectionNo 32A
  orderNo 33
  title `Non-resumption of cohabitation or restitution of conjugal rights within one year in pursuance of a decree to be ground for divorce.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30047&sectionno=32A&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_32_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[32A. Non-resumption of cohabitation or restitution of conjugal rights within one year in`
  line `pursuance of a decree to be ground for divorce.(1) Either party to a marriage, whether`
  line `solemnized before or after the commencement of the Parsi Marriage and Divorce (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1988 (5 of 1988), may sue for divorce also on the ground,`
  line
  line `(i) that there has been no resumption of cohabitation as between the parties to the marriage for a`
  line `period of one year or upwards after the passing of a decree for judicial separation in a proceeding to`
  line `which they were parties; or`
  line
  line `(ii) that there has been no restitution of conjugal rights as between the parties to the marriage for`
  line `a period of one year or upwards after the passing of a decree for restitution of conjugal rights in a`
  line `proceeding to which they were parties.`
  line
  line `(2) No decree for divorce shall be granted under sub-section (1) if the plaintiff has failed or neglected`
  line `to comply with an order for maintenance passed against him under section 40 of this Act or section 488 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1898 (5of 1898) or section 125 of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973`
  line `(2 of 1974).`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b:
  sectionId (30048)
  sectionNo 32B
  orderNo 34
  title `Divorce by mutual consent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30048&sectionno=32B&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_content:
  string
  line `[32B. Divorce by mutual consent.—(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, a suit for divorce may`
  line `be filed by both the parties to a marriage together, whether such marriage was solemnized before or after`
  line `the commencement of the Parsi Marriage and Divorce (Amendment) Act, 1988 (5 of 1988), on the`
  line `ground that they have been living separately for a period of one year or more, that they have not been able`
  line `to live together and that they have mutually agreed that the marriage should be dissolved:`
  line
  line `Provided that no suit under this sub-section shall be filed unless at the date of the filing of the suit one`
  line `year has lapsed since the date of the marriage.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court shall, on being satisfied, after hearing the parties and after making such inquiry as it`
  line `thinks fit, that a marriage has been solemnized under this Act and the averments in the plaint are true and`
  line `that the consent of either party to the suit was not obtained by force or fraud, pass a decree declaring the`
  line `marriage to be dissolved with effect from the date of the decree.]`
obj_root_law_sections_32_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_33:
  sectionId (30049)
  sectionNo (33)
  orderNo 35
  title `Joining of co-defendant.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_33_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30049&sectionno=33&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_33_content:
  string
  line `In every such suit for divorce on the ground of adultery, the plaintiff`
  line `shall, unless the Court shall otherwise order, make the person with whom the adultery is alleged to have`
  line `been committed a co-defendant, and in any such suit by the husband the Court may order the adulterer to`
  line `pay the whole or any part of the costs of the proceedings.`
obj_root_law_sections_33_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_34:
  sectionId (30050)
  sectionNo (34)
  orderNo 36
  title `Suits for judicial separation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_34_content
  footnotes `1. Certain words omitted by Act 5 of 1988, s. 10 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30050&sectionno=34&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_34_content:
  string
  line `Any married person may sue for judicial separation on any of the`
  line `grounds for which such person could have filed a suit for divorce ^1***.`
obj_root_law_sections_35:
  sectionId (30051)
  sectionNo (35)
  orderNo 37
  title `Decrees in certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_35_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 11, bid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30051&sectionno=35&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_35_content:
  string
  line `In any suit under section 30, 31, 32, ^1[32A] or 34, whether defended`
  line `or not, if the Court be satisfied that any of the grounds set forth in those sections for granting relief exist,`
  line `that none of the grounds therein set forth for withholding relief exist and that--`
  line
  line `(a) the act or omission set forth in the plaint has not been condoned;`
  line
  line `(b) the husband and wife are not colluding together;`
  line
  line `(c) the plaintiff has not connived at or been accessory to the said act or omission;`
  line
  line `(d) (save where a definite period of limitation is provided by this Act) there has been no`
  line `unnecessary or improper delay in instituting the suit; and`
  line
  line `(e) there is no other legal ground why relief should not be granted;`
  line
  line `then and in such case, but not otherwise, the Court shall decree such relief accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_36:
  sectionId (30052)
  sectionNo (36)
  orderNo 38
  title `Suit for restitution of conjugal rights.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_36_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30052&sectionno=36&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_36_content:
  string
  line `Where a husband shall have deserted or without lawful`
  line `cause ceased to cohabit with his wife, or where a wife shall have deserted or without lawful cause ceased`
  line `to cohabit with her husband, the party so deserted or with whom cohabitation shall have so ceased may`
  line `sue for the restitution of his or her conjugal rights and the Court, if satisfied of the truth of the allegations`
  line `contained in the plaint, and that there is no just ground why relief should not be granted, may proceed to`
  line `decree such restitution of conjugal rights accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_36_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_37:
  sectionId (30053)
  sectionNo (37)
  orderNo 39
  title `Counter-claim by defendant for any relief.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_37_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30053&sectionno=37&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_37_content:
  string
  line `In any suit under this Act, the defendant may`
  line `make a counter claim for any relief he or she may be entitled to under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_37_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_38:
  sectionId (30054)
  sectionNo (38)
  orderNo 40
  title `Documentary evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_38_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 12, ibid., for section 38 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30054&sectionno=38&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_38_content:
  string
  line `^1[Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time`
  line `being in force, no document shall be inadmissible in evidence in any proceeding at the trial of a suit under`
  line `this Act on the ground that it is not duly stamped or registered.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39:
  sectionId (30055)
  sectionNo (39)
  orderNo 41
  title `Alimony pendente lite.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_39_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30055&sectionno=39&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_39_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where in any suit under this Act, it appears to the Court that either the`
  line `wife or the husband, as the case may be, has no independent income sufficient for her or his support and`
  line `the necessary expenses of the suit, it may, on the application of the wife or the husband, order the`
  line `defendant to pay to the plaintiff, the expenses of the suit, and such weekly or monthly sum, during the`
  line `suit, as, having regard to the plaintiff's own income and the income of the defendant, it may seem to the`
  line `Court to be reasonable:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the application for the payment of the expenses of the suit and such weekly or`
  line `monthly sum during the suit, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days from the date of`
  line `service of notice on the wife or the husband, as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_39_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 13, for sections 39 and 40 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_40:
  sectionId (30056)
  sectionNo (40)
  orderNo 42
  title `Permanent alimony and maintenance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_40_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30056&sectionno=40&orderno=42&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_40_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any Court exercising jurisdiction under this Act`
  line `may, at the time of passing any decree or at any time subsequent thereto, on an application made to it for`
  line `the purpose by either the wife or the husband, order that the defendant shall pay to the plaintiff for her or`
  line `his maintenance and support, such gross sum or such monthly or periodical sum, for a term not exceeding`
  line `the life of the plaintiff as having regard to the defendant's own income and other property, if any, the`
  line `income and other property of the plaintiff, the conduct of the parties and other circumstances of the case,`
  line `it may seem to the Court to be just, and any such payment may be secured, if necessary, by a charge on`
  line `the movable or immovable property of the defendant.`
  line
  line `(2) The Court if it is satisfied that there is change in the circumstances of either party at any time after`
  line `it has made an order under sub-section (1), it may, at the instance of either party, vary, modify or rescind`
  line `any such order in such manner as the Court may deem just.`
  line
  line `(3) The Court if it is satisfied that the party in whose favour an order has been made under this section`
  line `has remarried or, if such party is the wife, that she has not remained chaste, or, if such party is the`
  line `husband, that he had sexual intercourse with any woman outside wedlock, it may, at the instance of the`
  line `other party, vary, modify or rescind any such order in such manner as the Court may deem just.`
obj_root_law_sections_40_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_41:
  sectionId (30057)
  sectionNo (41)
  orderNo 43
  title `Payment of alimony to wife or to her trustee.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_41_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 5 of 1988, s. 14 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30057&sectionno=41&orderno=43&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_41_content:
  string
  line `In all cases in which the Court shall make any`
  line `decree or order for alimony it may direct the same to be paid either to the wife herself, or to any trustee on`
  line `her behalf to be approved by the Court 3`
  line `or to a guardian appointed by the Court, and may impose any`
  line `terms or restrictions which to the Court may seem expedient, and may from time to time appoint a new`
  line trustee,
  line `^1[or guardian], if for any reason it shall appear to the Court expedient so to do.`
obj_root_law_sections_42:
  sectionId (30058)
  sectionNo (42)
  orderNo 44
  title `Disposal of joint property.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_42_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30058&sectionno=42&orderno=44&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_42_content:
  string
  line `In any suit under this Act the Court may make such provisions in`
  line `the final decree as it may deem just and proper with respect to property presented at or about the time of`
  line `marriage which may belong jointly to both the husband and wife.`
obj_root_law_sections_42_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_43:
  sectionId (30059)
  sectionNo (43)
  orderNo 45
  title `Suits to be heard in camera and may not be printed or published.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_43_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 15, ibid., for section 43 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988)`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30059&sectionno=43&orderno=45&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_43_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Every suit filed`
  line `under this Act shall be tried in camera and it shall not be lawful for any person to print or publish any`
  line `matter in relation to any such case except a judgment of the Court printed or published with the previous`
  line `permission of the Court.`
  line
  line `(2) If any person prints or publishes any matter in contravention of the provisions contained in subsection (1), he shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.]`
obj_root_law_sections_44:
  sectionId (30060)
  sectionNo (44)
  orderNo 46
  title `Validity of trial.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_44_content
  footnotes `32. Subs. by s. 16, ibid., for “five” (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30060&sectionno=44&orderno=46&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_44_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in section 19 or section 20 where in the`
  line `case of a trial in a Parsi Matrimonial Court not less than ^32`
  line `three delegates have attended throughout the`
  line `proceedings, the trial shall not be invalid by reason of the absence during any part thereof of the other`
  line delegates.
obj_root_law_sections_45:
  sectionId (30061)
  sectionNo (45)
  orderNo 47
  title `Provisions of Civil Procedure Code to apply to suits under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_45_content
  footnotes `1. Added by Act 5 of 1988, s. 17 (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30061&sectionno=45&orderno=47&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_45_content:
  string
  line `The provisions of the`
  line `Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), shall, so far as the same may be applicable, apply to`
  line `proceedings in suits instituted under this Act including proceedings in execution and orders subsequent to`
  line `decree:`
  line
  line `^1[Provided that the presiding Judge shall read out to the delegates the relevant sections of this Act,`
  line `and may, if he considers it necessary so to do, explain the same:`
  line
  line `Provided further that a verbatim record shall be made of what the presiding Judge read out or explains`
  line `to the delegates.]`
obj_root_law_sections_46:
  sectionId (30062)
  sectionNo (46)
  orderNo 48
  title `Determination of questions of law and procedure and of fact.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_46_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30062&sectionno=46&orderno=48&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_46_content:
  string
  line `In suits under this Act all`
  line `questions of law and procedure shall be determined by the presiding Judge; but the decision on the facts`
  line `shall be the decision of the majority of the delegates before whom the case is tried:`
  line `Provided that, where such delegates are equally divided in opinion, the decision on the facts shall be`
  line `the decision of the presiding Judge.`
obj_root_law_sections_46_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_47:
  sectionId (30063)
  sectionNo (47)
  orderNo 49
  title `Appeal to High Court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_47_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30063&sectionno=47&orderno=49&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_47_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] An appeal shall lie to the High Court from--`
  line
  line `(a) the decision of any Court established under this Act, whether a Chief Matrimonial Court or`
  line `District Matrimonial Court, on the ground of the decision being contrary to some law or usage having`
  line `the force of law, or of a substantial error or defect in the procedure or investigation of the case which`
  line `may have produced error or defect in the decision of the case upon the merits, and on no other`
  line `ground; and`
  line
  line `(b) the granting of leave by any such Court under sub-section (3) of section 29:`
  line
  line `Provided that such appeal shall be instituted within three calendar months after the decision`
  line `appealed from shall have been pronounced.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) Every appeal under sub-section (1) shall be heard by a Bench of two Judges of the High Court.]`
obj_root_law_sections_47_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 47 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by s. 18,ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by s. 18, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_48:
  sectionId (30064)
  sectionNo (48)
  orderNo 50
  title `Liberty to parties to marry again.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_48_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30064&sectionno=48&orderno=50&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_48_content:
  string
  line `When the time ^1*** limited for appealing against any`
  line `decree granting a divorce or annulling or dissolving a marriage shall have expired, and no appeal shall`
  line `have been presented against such decree, or when any such appeal shall have been dismissed, or when in`
  line `the result of any appeal a divorce has been granted or a marriage has been declared to be annulled or`
  line `dissolved, but not sooner, it shall be lawful for the respective parties thereto to marry again ^2***.`
obj_root_law_sections_48_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The word "hereby" omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. The words ", as if the prior marriage had been terminated by death" omitted by s. 19, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
obj_root_law_sections_49:
  sectionId (30065)
  sectionNo (49)
  orderNo 51
  title `Custody of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_49_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30065&sectionno=49&orderno=51&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_49_content:
  string
  line `In any suit under this Act, the Court may from time to time pass such`
  line `interim orders and make such provisions in the final decree as it may deem just and proper with respect to`
  line `the custody, maintenance and education of the children under the age of ^1[eighteen years], the marriage of`
  line `of whose parents is the subject of such suit, and may, after the final decree upon application, by petition`
  line `for this purpose, make, revoke, suspend or vary from time to time all such orders and provisions with`
  line `respect to the custody, maintenance and education of such children as might have been made by such`
  line `final decree or by interim orders in case the suit for obtaining such decree were still pending:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the application with respect to the maintenance and education of such children during`
  line `the suit, shall, as far as possible, be disposed of within sixty days from the date of service of notice on the`
  line respondent.]
obj_root_law_sections_49_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 20, ibid., for "sixteen years" (w.e.f. 15-4-1988).`
  line `2. Ins. by Act 49 of 2001, s. 4 (w.e.f. 24-9-2001).`
obj_root_law_sections_50:
  sectionId (30066)
  sectionNo (50)
  orderNo 52
  title `Settlement of wife’s property for benefit of children.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_50_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30066&sectionno=50&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_50_content:
  string
  line `In any case in which the Court shall`
  line `pronounce a decree of divorce or judicial separation for adultery of the wife, if it shall be made to appear`
  line `to the Court that the wife is entitled to any property either in possession or reversion, the Court may order`
  line `such settlement as it shall think reasonable to be made of any part of such property, not exceeding`
  line `one half thereof, for the benefit of the children of the marriage or any of them.`
obj_root_law_sections_50_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_51:
  sectionId (30067)
  sectionNo (51)
  orderNo 53
  title `Superintendence of High court.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_51_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30067&sectionno=51&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_51_content:
  string
  line `The High Court shall have superintendence over all Courts`
  line `constituted under this Act subject to its appellate jurisdiction in the same manner as it has over other`
  line `Courts under ^1[article 227 of the Constitution] and all the provisions of ^2[that article] shall apply to such`
  line Courts
obj_root_law_sections_51_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by the A.O. 1950, for "section 107 of the Government of India Act".`
  line `2. Subs. by Act 3 of 1957, s. 3 and the Second Schedule for "that section" (w.e.f. 17-9-1957).`
obj_root_law_sections_52:
  sectionId (30068)
  sectionNo (52)
  orderNo 54
  title `Applicability of provisions of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_52_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30068&sectionno=52&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_52_content:
  string
  line `(1) The provisions of this Act shall apply to all suits to`
  line `which the same are applicable whether the circumstances relied on occurred before or after the passing of`
  line `this Act, and whether any decree or order referred to was passed under this Act or under the law in force`
  line `before the passing of this Act, and where any proceedings are pending in any Court at the time of the`
  line `commencement of this Act, the Court shall allow such amendment of the pleadings as may be necessary`
  line `as the result of the coming into operation of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A Parsi who has contracted a marriage under the Parsi Marriage and Divorce Act, 1865 (15 of`
  line `1865), or under this Act, even though such Parsi may change his or her religion or domicile, so long as his`
  line `or her wife or husband is alive and so long as such Parsi has not been lawfully divorced from such wife or`
  line `husband or such marriage has not lawfully been declared null and void or dissolved under the decree of a`
  line `competent Court under either of the said Acts, shall remain bound by the provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_52_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_53:
  sectionId (30069)
  sectionNo (53)
  orderNo 55
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_53_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943&sectionId=30069&sectionno=53&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00076_1936-03_1535537599943
obj_root_law_sections_53_content:
  string
  line `Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act, 1937 (20 of 1937), s. 3 and the Second`
  line Schedule.
obj_root_law_sections_53_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_translations:
  hi obj_root_law_translations_hi
